Class FileSystemElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • FileSystemElement
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Directory, File
    public abstract class FileSystemElement
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a file system element.

    This class is used to represent a file system element.

    It is the superclass of the Directory and File classes.

    It contains the name of the file system element, the date created, and the parent directory.

    The class has the following methods:

    • FileSystemElement(String, FileSystemElement): Creates a new file system element with a name and a parent directory.
    • FileSystemElement(String, FileSystemElement, Timestamp): Creates a new file system element with a name, a parent directory, and a creation date.
    • getName(): Returns the name of the file system element.
    • getDateCreated(): Returns the date created.
    • getParent(): Returns the parent directory.
    • setParent(FileSystemElement): Sets the parent directory.
    • getFullPath(): Returns the full path of the file system element.
    • print(String): Prints the file system element with a prefix.
    • saveElement(PrintWriter): Saves the file system element to a file.
